      "paper_id": "THIACC002",
      "title": "Dark Current and Halo Tracking in ERLs",
      "authors": [
        "HZB",
        "Berlin",
        "Germany",
        "Particles that are far from the core of a bunch are often lost in an uncontrolled way within an accelerator",
        "and in high-current machines beam loss can quickly damage accelerator components or cause significant residual activation. We give a brief overview of the common sources of unwanted beam",
        "including halo generated by nonlinear dynamics",
        "dark current from field emission in the cavities",
        "out-of-time scattered laser light on the cathode",
        "and incompletely blocked laser pulses. The results of tracking simulations to model these effects in BERLinPro are discussed."
